Thermedics Inc. said it will redeem its 5.5% convertible subordinated debentures due 1996 on Oct. 31, 

The redemption price is 103% of the principal amount plus accrued interest to the redemption date.
The biomedical products maker said there are about $3 million principal amount of the debentures outstanding. 

Until Oct. 31, holders of debentures have the option of converting their debentures into common stock at a conversion price of $11.58 a share, the company said. 

Based on the closing price of Thermedics common stock on the American Stock Exchange on Sept. 27, 86,356 shares of common stock for each $1,000 principal amount of converted debentures has a current market value of about $1,630. 

